#### Step 1: Drift Detection (`drift_detector.c/h`)

The `DriftDetector` continuously monitors model metrics. When a metric exceeds the configured threshold, drift is detected.

**File**: `src/controller/monitoring/drift_detector.c`, lines 177-234

```c
int drift_detector_update_metric(const char *model_id, double metric_value) {
    // ... lookup model state ...

    // Page-Hinkley test computation
    state->cumulative_sum += (metric_value - state->x_mean - state->delta);
    double ph_statistic = state->cumulative_sum - state->min_cumulative_sum;

    // Drift detected?
    if (ph_statistic > state->lambda) {
        char reason[128];
        snprintf(reason, sizeof(reason),
                 "Drift detected (PH=%.4f > λ=%.4f) after %zu samples",
                 ph_statistic, state->lambda, state->sample_count);

        // Notify observers (releases lock first to avoid deadlocks)
        callback_node_t *tmp_callbacks = g_callbacks;
        pthread_mutex_unlock(&g_lock);

        while (tmp_callbacks) {
            tmp_callbacks->fn(model_id, reason, tmp_callbacks->user_data);
            tmp_callbacks = tmp_callbacks->next;
        }
        // ... reset state for next cycle ...
    }
}
```

The drift detector uses the **Page-Hinkley test** for change detection and notifies all registered callbacks when drift exceeds `lambda`.

#### Step 2: Model Monitor Aggregation (`model_monitor.c/h`)

The `ModelMonitor` aggregates monitoring events and performs periodic surveillance. It detects drift based on accuracy/loss thresholds.

**File**: `src/controller/monitoring/model_monitor.c`, lines 191-233

```c
static void *monitor_loop(void *arg) {
    ll_model_monitor *mon = arg;

    while (mon->running) {
        double live_acc = 0.0, live_loss = 0.0;
        long   ts       = 0L;

        if (!acquire_live_metrics(mon, &live_acc, &live_loss, &ts)) {
            goto sleep_and_continue;
        }

        if (drift_detected(mon, live_acc, live_loss)) {
            ll_drift_event ev = {
                .model_id         = mon->model_id,
                .live_accuracy    = live_acc,
                .live_loss        = live_loss,
                .baseline_accuracy= mon->baseline_accuracy,
                .baseline_loss    = mon->baseline_loss,
                .timestamp        = ts
            };

            ll_log_warn("[Monitor:%s] DRIFT detected (live_acc=%.4f, baseline=%.4f)",
                        mon->model_id, live_acc, mon->baseline_accuracy);

            notify_observers(mon, &ev);  // Notify registered observers

            if (mon->cfg.auto_refresh_baseline)
                refresh_baseline(mon);
        }
        sleep_interrupible(mon->cfg.poll_interval_sec);
    }
}
```

#### Step 3: Retraining Trigger Evaluation (`retraining_trigger.c/h`)

The `RetrainingTrigger` component decides whether retraining is warranted based on drift severity and policy rules.

**File**: `src/controller/monitoring/retraining_trigger.c`, lines 343-400

```c
static bool _rt_drift_detected(rt_model_entry_t *ent) {
    if (ent->count < RT_BASELINE_WINDOW * 2) { return false; }

    double baseline = _rt_avg_first_n(ent, RT_BASELINE_WINDOW);
    double current  = _rt_avg_last_n(ent,  RT_BASELINE_WINDOW);

    if (baseline == 0.0) { return false; }

    double delta_pct;
    if (ent->metric_type == RT_METRIC_LOSS) {
        // Increase in loss indicates drift
        delta_pct = ((current - baseline) / baseline) * 100.0;
        return delta_pct >= ent->drift_threshold_pct;
    } else {
        // Decrease in metric (accuracy, F1, etc.) indicates drift
        delta_pct = ((baseline - current) / baseline) * 100.0;
        return delta_pct >= ent->drift_threshold_pct;
    }
}

void rt_check_and_schedule(void) {
    // ... scan registry for drift ...
    for (size_t i = 0; i < RT_MAX_MODELS; ++i) {
        if (_rt_drift_detected(ent)) {
            ent->retrain_pending = true;
            pthread_mutex_unlock(&_rt_state.mtx);

            bool ok = _rt_state.callback(ent->model_id);  // Trigger retraining

            pthread_mutex_lock(&_rt_state.mtx);
            if (ok) {
                ent->count = 0;
                ent->head = 0;
                ent->retrain_pending = false;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

